        "Splitting this out from #3064:\n\n> We should use the following structure:\n> \n> ``` python\n> {'resources': {\n>    'cluster_port': 29015,\n>    'host': u'127.0.0.1',\n>    'http_admin_port': 8080,\n>    'reql_port': 28015\n>    'cache_size_mb': 2042.064453125,\n>    'pid': 53646,\n>  },\n>  'status': u'available',\n>  'connectivity': {\n>    'time_connected': datetime.datetime(2014, 9, 16, 19, 47, 7, 787000, tzinfo=<rethinkdb.ast.RqlTzinfo object at 0x10e3ed190>),\n>    'time_disconnected': None,\n>    'time_started': datetime.datetime(2014, 9, 16, 19, 47, 7, 784000, tzinfo=<rethinkdb.ast.RqlTzinfo object at 0x10e3ed150>),\n>  },\n>  'name': u'batgirl_local_9d7',\n>  'id': u'bbab4f0e-3e33-4c5e-bb3d-6bbe8a196af6'}]\n> ```\n> \n> And here is the structure we should use for a disconnected/unavailable server:\n> \n> ``` python\n> { 'status': u'unreachable',\n>   'resources': {\n>    'cluster_port': None,\n>    'host': u'127.0.0.1',\n>    'http_admin_port': None,\n>    'reql_port': None,\n>    'cache_size_mb': None,\n>    'pid': None,\n>  },\n>  'connectivity': {\n>    'time_connected': None,\n>    'time_disconnected': datetime.datetime(2014, 9, 16, 20, 45, 48, 85000, tzinfo=<rethinkdb.ast.RqlTzinfo object at 0x10e3ed110>),\n>    'time_started': None,\n>  },\n>  'name': u'batgirl_local_9d7',\n>  'id': u'bbab4f0e-3e33-4c5e-bb3d-6bbe8a196af6'}]\n> ```\n\nAlso, we should figure out how to present host/port information. The current implementation has a field `hostname` with the return value of `gethostname()`, and a series of `port` fields with what the server thinks it's ports are. We should also think about #3179 and whether we should present canonical addresses somehow. @Tryneus, do you have any suggestions?\n"
